Please verify any debt you are attempting to collect from me as required by the
Fair Debt Collection Practices Act (FDCPA) section 1692g and New York City
Administrative Code section 20-493.2. Please note that New York City rules
require all debt collectors to send specific written documentation verifying the
debt. Under section 2-190 of the Rules of the City of New York, verification
• Proof of my agreement to pay the original creditor.
• A copy of the final account statement issued by the original creditor.
• A breakdown of the total amount due, showing principal, interest, and other
charges. For all other charges, the date of and basis for each charge.
• Confirm that the statute of limitations period has not passed.
Aside from verifying the debt, do not contact me again about this debt. The
FDCPA and section 5-77 of the Rules of the City of New York require that you
I dispute this debt because I am a victim of identity theft. Because I am
disputing this debt, you should not report it to the credit reporting agencies. If
you have already reported it, please notify the credit reporting agencies that the
debt is disputed and/or delete the tradeline from my credit report. Reporting
information that you know to be inaccurate, or failing to report information
correctly, violates the FDCPA and the Fair Credit Reporting Act.
